  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3 \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A report issued by the Sri Lankan Bar Association",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Bar Association of Sri Lanka has requested all party leaders to act swiftly to rebuild public confidence in Sri Lanka's legal and constitutional mechanisms.",
        "It is titled Statement of the Sri Lankan Bar Association on the Resignation of President Gotabaya Rajapaksa.",
        "The President of the Sri Lanka Bar Association, President Advocate Saliya Peiris, and Secretary Advocate Isuru Balapattabendi have signed it.",
        "In a situation where the country is suffering from social, political and economic instability, it has been mentioned in the statement issued by the Bar Association that members of parliament should act quickly to avoid further deterioration of the situation. (a)"
      ],
